The national government has officially opened the 52nd Huduma Centre in Tana River county set up at a cost of Sh42 million. The ultra-modern facility is located at Hola in Galole constituency and will enable residents to receive government services in a one-stop shop like in other counties, which are already enjoying improved services. Speaking during the official launch Tana River county commissioner Oningoi ole Sosio told heads of departments to represent the state well and avoid portraying a bad image.